{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"4960d96ac8b4d76d","type":"text","text":"**THE SENATE**\n\n**Senate**\nA unicameral legislature composing of 138 members (three pairs of a man and a woman from each republic). It proposes and *evaluates* law, manages the economy, declares war, and elects members of the Secretariat-Directory.\n\n**Committees**\nMembers of the Senate and their associates form committees based on a certain topic to guide the executive departments of the secretariat.","x":-560,"y":-120,"width":405,"height":410},
		{"id":"ce4e63ab73ab35df","type":"text","text":"**THE SECRETARIAT**\n\n**Secretary-General**\nAn office elected by the Secretariat-Directory, functioning as a largely ceremonial head of state and government for the Commonwealth as a whole. The role is more diplomatic than it is executive. Elected to a maximum of two eight-year terms.\n\n**Secretariat-Directory**\nNine senators elected for four-year terms by the Senate. They compose the head of the executive branch and propose and approve law created by the Senate.\n\n**Cabinet**\nAn advisory body that supports the Secretariat-Directory. While members of the Directory are the *de jure* heads of the executive departments, the actual running if them is left to the undersecretaries that make up the cabinet. \n\n**Supreme Secretariat**\nAn informal body composed of the Secretariat-Directory and the Cabinet that deliberates on certain executive decisions. The Supreme Secretariat also includes members from prominent Senate committees, technical experts or state corporations.","x":-155,"y":-120,"width":405,"height":820},
		{"id":"0a5c9a3aac9793c1","type":"text","text":"**THE JUDICIARY**\n\n**Supreme Judiciary**\nThe highest court in the Commonwealth, made up of 7 justices who serve 20-year terms. Justices are appointed by the Secretariat-Directory and the Senate, and approved by the people of the Commonwealth. Justices interpret law approved by the Senate and Secretariat to determine if it is constitutional.\n\n**Supreme Court of Appeals**\nA *parallel court* to the Supreme Judiciary that judges high-profile cases and upholds human rights within the Commonwealth.","x":250,"y":-120,"width":390,"height":440},
		{"id":"d8a59aa04c4d8e5d","type":"text","text":"**THE DEPARTMENTS**\n\n**Departmental Assemblies**\nSeveral consultative bodies comprising the heads of each devolved and federal department (taken from the cabinet). Primarily used to assist in operating government-owned corporations or other external bodies.\n\n**Federal Departments**\nThe highest level in departments that answers directly to the federal government. Federal departments administrate the overall running of a department across the entire Commonwealth.\n\n**Devolved Departments**\nThe lower half of departments that answer to the Commonwealth's republics. Devolved departments can also delegate power further to provincial and municipal governments.\n\n**Worker Assemblies**\nSmaller administrative bodies, composed of representatives of each Council, that elect the administrators of devolved departments. Assembly members often run for the Senate. \n\n**Worker Councils**\nWorker councils function like small trade unions, and exist in virtually every profession in the Commonwealth. Worker councils democratically elect their leaders and collectively make local decisions on their behalf.","x":-155,"y":700,"width":405,"height":920},
		{"id":"6dcae51cda43abba","type":"text","text":"**THE CONSTITUENT BODIES**\n\n**Republics**\nThe first-level subdivisions of the Rosen government. Republics receive a great deal of autonomy and maintain their own devolved departments under the federal Secretariat.\n\n**Provinces**\nProvinces are the larger subdivisions within Republics, managing local governance in rural and suburban areas.\n\n**Municipalities**\nMunicipalities are smaller than provinces and govern urban areas and the economic centers of provinces. Some, more rural provinces will have no municipalities, whereas more urbanized republics will have several municipalities.","x":-560,"y":290,"width":405,"height":540}
	],
	"edges":[]
}